{-

 This file contains a proof of the following fact:
 for a commutative ring R with elements f and g s.t.
 ⟨f,g⟩ = R, we get a get a pullback square

                 _/1
            R   ----> R[1/f]
              ⌟
       _/1  |         | χ₁
            v         v

            R[1/g] -> R[1/fg]
                   χ₂

 where the morphisms χ are induced by the universal property
 of localization.

 -}


